<paragraph blockId="2.[189,549,1266,1293]" box="[189,549,1266,1293]" pageId="2" pageNumber="125">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,549,1266,1293]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="2" pageNumber="125" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,549,1266,1293]" pageId="2" pageNumber="125">
The 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[245,374,1266,1293]" class="Insecta" family="Fulgoridae" genus="Pyrops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="candelaria">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[245,374,1266,1293]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="125">candelaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[189,1392,1316,1498]" box="[189,1062,1316,1343]" pageId="2" pageNumber="125">
The characters of this group mainly follow 
<bibRefCitation author="Baker C. F." box="[698,933,1316,1343]" pageId="2" pageNumber="125" pagination="343 - 364" refId="ref9803" refString="Baker C. F. 1925. Remarks on certain Indo-Malayan Fulgora, with special reference to Philippines species. Philippines Journal of Science 28: 343 - 364." type="journal article" year="1925">Baker’s (1925: 348)</bibRefCitation>
definition:
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="126" pageId="2" pageNumber="125" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="2.[189,1392,1316,1498]" pageId="2" pageNumber="125">(1) cephalic process long and slender, usually strongly upcurved, sometimes oblique to nearly straight; (2) apex of cephalic process compressed laterally, rarely very slightly swelling at apex;</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[189,1392,1316,1498]" box="[189,1085,1433,1459]" pageId="2" pageNumber="125">(3) tegmina with transverse bands or transversely aligned spots or markings;</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[189,1392,1316,1498]" box="[189,594,1472,1498]" pageId="2" pageNumber="125">(4) hind wings variously coloured.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[187,1399,1541,1917]" pageId="2" pageNumber="125">
The group contains the 
<typeStatus box="[458,508,1541,1567]" pageId="2" pageNumber="125">type</typeStatus>
species of the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Spinola" authorityYear="1839" box="[747,828,1542,1567]" class="Insecta" family="Fulgoridae" genus="Pyrops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[747,828,1542,1567]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="125">Pyrops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[843,996,1541,1567]" class="Insecta" family="Fulgoridae" genus="Pyrops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="candelaria">
<emphasis box="[843,996,1541,1567]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="125">P. candelaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and is the most species-rich group within the genus. 
<bibRefCitation author="Nagai S. &amp; Porion T." box="[400,673,1580,1607]" pageId="2" pageNumber="125" refId="ref11134" refString="Nagai S. &amp; Porion T. 1996. Fulgoridae 2: Catalogue illustre des Faunes asiatique et australienne. Sciences Nat, Compiegne." type="book" year="1996">Nagai &amp; Porion (1996)</bibRefCitation>
listed 25 species in the group and more recently a number of species were added: 
<taxonomicName authority="(Distant, 1906)" authorityName="" baseAuthorityName="Distant" baseAuthorityYear="1906" box="[432,730,1618,1645]" class="Insecta" family="Fulgoridae" genus="Pyrops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rogersi">
<emphasis box="[432,545,1619,1644]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="125">P. rogersi</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Distant W. L." box="[560,721,1618,1645]" pageId="2" pageNumber="125" refId="ref10413" refString="Distant W. L. 1906. Rhynchota Vol. 3. Heteroptera-Homoptera. In: C. T. Bingham (ed.) The Fauna of British India, including Ceylon and Burma. Taylor and Francis, London. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 48423" type="book" year="1906">Distant, 1906</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
was transferred from the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Donovan" baseAuthorityYear="1800" box="[1033,1193,1618,1644]" class="Insecta" family="Fulgoridae" genus="Pyrops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pyrorhynchus">
<emphasis box="[1033,1193,1618,1644]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="125">pyrorhynchus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group by 
<bibRefCitation author="Constant J. &amp; Mohan A. V." box="[189,493,1657,1683]" pageId="2" pageNumber="125" pagination="1 - 24" refId="ref10257" refString="Constant J. &amp; Mohan A. V. 2017. The lanternflies from Andaman and Nicobar: one new Pyrops species, new records and illustrated key to the species (Hemiptera: Fulgoromorpha: Fulgoridae). Belgian Journal of Entomology 49: 1 - 24." type="journal article" year="2017">Constant &amp; Mohan (2017)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Baker, 1925)" baseAuthorityName="Baker" baseAuthorityYear="1925" box="[503,865,1657,1684]" class="Insecta" family="Fulgoridae" genus="Pyrops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maquilinganus">
<emphasis box="[503,702,1657,1683]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="125">P. maquilinganus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Baker C. F." box="[716,857,1657,1684]" pageId="2" pageNumber="125" pagination="343 - 364" refId="ref9803" refString="Baker C. F. 1925. Remarks on certain Indo-Malayan Fulgora, with special reference to Philippines species. Philippines Journal of Science 28: 343 - 364." type="journal article" year="1925">Baker, 1925</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
was transferred from the 
<emphasis box="[1156,1236,1657,1683]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="125">effusus</emphasis>
species group by 
<bibRefCitation author="Constant J." box="[225,416,1696,1723]" pageId="2" pageNumber="125" pagination="1 - 23" refId="ref10108" refString="Constant J. 2015. Review of the effusus group of the Lanternfly genus Pyrops Spinola, 1839, with one new species and notes on trophobiosis (Hemiptera: Fulgoromorpha: Fulgoridae). European Journal of Taxonomy 128: 1 - 23. https: // doi. org / 10.5852 / ejt. 2015.128" type="journal article" year="2015">Constant (2015)</bibRefCitation>
and eight additional species were described: 
<taxonomicName authority="Constant, 2021" authorityName="Constant" authorityYear="2021" box="[957,1265,1696,1722]" class="Insecta" family="Fulgoridae" genus="Pyrops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="auratus">
<emphasis box="[957,1077,1697,1722]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="125">P. auratus</emphasis>
Constant, 2021
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Constant &amp; Mohan, 2017" authorityName="Constant &amp; Mohan" authorityYear="2017" class="Insecta" family="Fulgoridae" genus="Pyrops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="azureus">
<emphasis box="[1278,1398,1697,1722]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="125">P. azureus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Constant J. &amp; Mohan A. V." box="[189,497,1735,1761]" pageId="2" pageNumber="125" pagination="1 - 24" refId="ref10257" refString="Constant J. &amp; Mohan A. V. 2017. The lanternflies from Andaman and Nicobar: one new Pyrops species, new records and illustrated key to the species (Hemiptera: Fulgoromorpha: Fulgoridae). Belgian Journal of Entomology 49: 1 - 24." type="journal article" year="2017">Constant &amp; Mohan, 2017</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Chew Kea Foo, Porion &amp; Audibert, 2010" authorityName="Chew Kea Foo, Porion &amp; Audibert" authorityYear="2010" box="[511,1137,1735,1762]" class="Insecta" family="Fulgoridae" genus="Pyrops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jasmini">
<emphasis box="[511,629,1736,1761]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="125">P. jasmini</emphasis>
Chew Kea Foo, Porion &amp; Audibert, 2010
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Wang, Xu &amp; Qin, 2018" authorityName="Wang, Xu &amp; Qin" authorityYear="2018" class="Insecta" family="Fulgoridae" genus="Pyrops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jiangfenglingensis">
<emphasis box="[1150,1398,1735,1761]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="125">P. jiangfenglingensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Wang W. Q. &amp; Xu S. - L. &amp; Qin D. - Z." box="[189,472,1774,1800]" pageId="2" pageNumber="125" pagination="296 - 309" refId="ref11557" refString="Wang W. Q., Xu S. - L. &amp; Qin D. - Z. 2018. The lanternfly genus Pyrops Spinola (Hemiptera: Fulgoridae) from China with description of a new species. Entomotaxonomia 40 (4): 296 - 309. https: // doi. org / 10.11680 / entomotax. 2018031" type="journal article" year="2018">Wang, Xu &amp; Qin, 2018</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Porion &amp; Audibert, 2020" authorityName="Porion &amp; Audibert" authorityYear="2020" box="[486,909,1774,1800]" class="Insecta" family="Fulgoridae" genus="Pyrops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kozlovi">
<emphasis box="[486,599,1774,1800]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="125">P. kozlovi</emphasis>
Porion &amp; Audibert, 2020
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Nagai, Porion &amp; Audibert, 2017" authorityName="Nagai, Porion &amp; Audibert" authorityYear="2017" class="Insecta" family="Fulgoridae" genus="Pyrops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nishiguroi">
<emphasis box="[922,1073,1774,1800]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="125">P. nishiguroi</emphasis>
Nagai, Porion &amp; Audibert, 2017
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Nagai &amp; Porion, 2002" authorityName="Nagai &amp; Porion" authorityYear="2002" box="[263,688,1813,1839]" class="Insecta" family="Fulgoridae" genus="Pyrops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nishiyamai">
<emphasis box="[263,421,1813,1839]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="125">P. nishiyamai</emphasis>
Nagai &amp; Porion, 2002
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Nagai, Porion &amp; Audibert, 2016" authorityName="Nagai, Porion &amp; Audibert" authorityYear="2016" box="[746,1271,1813,1839]" class="Insecta" family="Fulgoridae" genus="Pyrops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="priscillae">
<emphasis box="[746,886,1813,1839]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="125">P. priscillae</emphasis>
Nagai, Porion &amp; Audibert, 2016
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Bourgoin T." pageId="2" pageNumber="125" refId="ref9833" refString="Bourgoin T. 2021. FLOW (Fulgoromorpha Lists on The Web): a world knowledge base dedicated to Fulgoromorpha. Version 8, [3 Feb. 2022]. Available from http: // hemiptera-databases. org / flow / [accessed 8 Mar. 2022]." type="url" year="2021">Bourgoin 2021</bibRefCitation>
). Finally, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Kirby, 1818)" baseAuthorityName="Kirby" baseAuthorityYear="1818" box="[369,729,1851,1878]" class="Insecta" family="Fulgoridae" genus="Pyrops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lathburii">
<emphasis box="[369,561,1851,1877]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="125">Pyrops lathburii</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Kirby W. F." box="[577,721,1851,1878]" pageId="2" pageNumber="125" pagination="375 - 453" refId="ref10857" refString="Kirby W. F. 1818. A century of insects, including several new genera described from his cabinet. The Transactions of the Linnean Society of London. Second series. Zoology 12 (2): 375 - 453. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1095 - 8339.1817. tb 00239. x" type="journal article" year="1818">Kirby, 1818</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
is here transferred to the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[1031,1158,1851,1877]" class="Insecta" family="Fulgoridae" genus="Pyrops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="candelaria">
<emphasis box="[1031,1158,1851,1877]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="125">candelaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group, from the 
<emphasis box="[232,403,1890,1916]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="125">pyrorrhynchus</emphasis>
species group.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[189,1398,1959,2025]" pageId="2" pageNumber="125">
It is widely distributed in the Oriental Region: from 
<collectingCountry box="[809,924,1959,1985]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="2" pageNumber="125">Sri Lanka</collectingCountry>
it extends over northern 
<collectingCountry box="[1222,1285,1959,1985]" name="India" pageId="2" pageNumber="125">India</collectingCountry>
, southern 
<collectingCountry box="[189,262,1998,2024]" name="China" pageId="2" pageNumber="125">China</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[273,362,1998,2024]" name="Taiwan" pageId="2" pageNumber="125">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
, all Indochina, the 
<collectingCountry box="[586,721,1998,2024]" name="Philippines" pageId="2" pageNumber="125">Philippines</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[732,840,1998,2024]" name="Malaysia" pageId="2" pageNumber="125">Malaysia</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[897,1011,1998,2024]" name="Indonesia" pageId="2" pageNumber="125">Indonesia</collectingCountry>
southwards to 
<collectingRegion box="[1189,1299,1998,2024]" country="Indonesia" name="Sulawesi Utara" pageId="2" pageNumber="125">Sulawesi</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[189,588,264,291]" box="[189,588,264,291]" pageId="3" pageNumber="126">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,588,264,291]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="3" pageNumber="126" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,588,264,291]" pageId="3" pageNumber="126">
The 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Donovan" baseAuthorityYear="1800" box="[245,413,264,291]" class="Insecta" family="Fulgoridae" genus="Pyrops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="126" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pyrorhynchus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[245,413,264,291]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="126">pyrorhynchus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[189,1399,311,550]" pageId="3" pageNumber="126">
The 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Donovan" baseAuthorityYear="1800" box="[242,402,311,337]" class="Insecta" family="Fulgoridae" genus="Pyrops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="126" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pyrorhynchus">
<emphasis box="[242,402,311,337]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="126">pyrorhynchus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group, as defined by 
<bibRefCitation author="Baker C. F." box="[746,964,311,338]" pageId="3" pageNumber="126" pagination="343 - 364" refId="ref9803" refString="Baker C. F. 1925. Remarks on certain Indo-Malayan Fulgora, with special reference to Philippines species. Philippines Journal of Science 28: 343 - 364." type="journal article" year="1925">Baker (1925: 347)</bibRefCitation>
, contains species characterized by: (1) large, stout, elongate body;
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[189,1399,311,550]" pageId="3" pageNumber="126">(2) long stout cephalic process, not tapering apically, with width in dorsal view about equal along distal ⅘ and height in lateral view about equal along distal ⅘; upper margin in lateral view abruptly bent beyond mid-length (apical part often slightly higher in lateral view); apically brightly coloured, yellow to red; (3) anteocular carina slightly extending on vertex;</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[189,1399,311,550]" box="[189,1185,522,550]" pageId="3" pageNumber="126">(4) hind wings bright blue on basal ⅓, with apex and posterior margin broadly black.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[189,1399,589,969]" pageId="3" pageNumber="126">
According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Baker C. F." box="[350,509,589,616]" pageId="3" pageNumber="126" pagination="343 - 364" refId="ref9803" refString="Baker C. F. 1925. Remarks on certain Indo-Malayan Fulgora, with special reference to Philippines species. Philippines Journal of Science 28: 343 - 364." type="journal article" year="1925">Baker (1925)</bibRefCitation>
, the group contained 
<taxonomicName authority="Schmidt, 1923" authorityName="Schmidt" authorityYear="1923" box="[761,1065,589,615]" class="Insecta" family="Fulgoridae" genus="Pyrops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="126" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="incertus">
<emphasis box="[761,884,590,615]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="126">P. incertus</emphasis>
Schmidt, 1923
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Donovan, 1800)" baseAuthorityName="Donovan" baseAuthorityYear="1800" class="Insecta" family="Fulgoridae" genus="Pyrops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="126" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pyrorhynchus">
<emphasis box="[1078,1267,589,615]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="126">P. pyrorhynchus</emphasis>
(Donovan, 1800)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Distant, 1891)" baseAuthorityName="Distant" baseAuthorityYear="1891" box="[310,622,624,650]" class="Insecta" family="Fulgoridae" genus="Pyrops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="126" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pythicus">
<emphasis box="[310,435,624,650]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="126">P. pythicus</emphasis>
(Distant, 1891)
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Lallemand V." box="[632,842,624,651]" pageId="3" pageNumber="126" pagination="1 - 99" refId="ref10944" refString="Lallemand V. 1963. Revision des Fulgoridae (Homoptera). Deuxieme partie. Faunes asiatique et australienne. Memoires de l'Institut royal des Sciences naturelles de Belgique (2 e serie) 75: 1 - 99." type="journal article" year="1963">Lallemand (1963)</bibRefCitation>
added seven species to the group by broadening its interpretation without providing any justification, and 
<bibRefCitation author="Nagai S. &amp; Porion T." box="[877,1156,659,686]" pageId="3" pageNumber="126" refId="ref11134" refString="Nagai S. &amp; Porion T. 1996. Fulgoridae 2: Catalogue illustre des Faunes asiatique et australienne. Sciences Nat, Compiegne." type="book" year="1996">Nagai &amp; Porion (1996)</bibRefCitation>
followed his views. More recently, 
<bibRefCitation author="Constant J. &amp; Mohan A. V." box="[371,687,695,721]" pageId="3" pageNumber="126" pagination="1 - 24" refId="ref10257" refString="Constant J. &amp; Mohan A. V. 2017. The lanternflies from Andaman and Nicobar: one new Pyrops species, new records and illustrated key to the species (Hemiptera: Fulgoromorpha: Fulgoridae). Belgian Journal of Entomology 49: 1 - 24." type="journal article" year="2017">Constant &amp; Mohan (2017)</bibRefCitation>
transferred one of these species, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Distant, 1906)" authorityName="" baseAuthorityName="Distant" baseAuthorityYear="1906" box="[1088,1394,695,722]" class="Insecta" family="Fulgoridae" genus="Pyrops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="126" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rogersi">
<emphasis box="[1088,1202,696,721]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="126">P. rogersi</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Distant W. L." box="[1219,1385,695,722]" pageId="3" pageNumber="126" refId="ref10413" refString="Distant W. L. 1906. Rhynchota Vol. 3. Heteroptera-Homoptera. In: C. T. Bingham (ed.) The Fauna of British India, including Ceylon and Burma. Taylor and Francis, London. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 48423" type="book" year="1906">Distant, 1906</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, from the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Donovan" baseAuthorityYear="1800" box="[297,457,730,756]" class="Insecta" family="Fulgoridae" genus="Pyrops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="126" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pyrorhynchus">
<emphasis box="[297,457,730,756]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="126">pyrorhynchus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[538,665,730,756]" class="Insecta" family="Fulgoridae" genus="Pyrops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="126" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="candelaria">
<emphasis box="[538,665,730,756]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="126">candelaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group, and two additional ones, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Kirby, 1818)" baseAuthorityName="Kirby" baseAuthorityYear="1818" box="[1050,1348,730,756]" class="Insecta" family="Fulgoridae" genus="Pyrops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="126" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lathburii">
<emphasis box="[1050,1182,730,756]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="126">P. lathburii</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Kirby W. F." box="[1197,1340,730,756]" pageId="3" pageNumber="126" pagination="375 - 453" refId="ref10857" refString="Kirby W. F. 1818. A century of insects, including several new genera described from his cabinet. The Transactions of the Linnean Society of London. Second series. Zoology 12 (2): 375 - 453. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1095 - 8339.1817. tb 00239. x" type="journal article" year="1818">Kirby, 1818</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Distant, 1914)" baseAuthorityName="Distant" baseAuthorityYear="1914" box="[189,487,765,792]" class="Insecta" family="Fulgoridae" genus="Pyrops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="126" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="astarte">
<emphasis box="[189,299,766,791]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="126">P. astarte</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Distant W. L." box="[315,478,765,792]" pageId="3" pageNumber="126" pagination="409 - 424" refId="ref10469" refString="Distant W. L. 1914. Some additions to the genera and species in the Homopterous family Fulgoridae. Annals and Magazine of Natural History. London. (Ser. 8) 13: 409 - 424. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222931408693503" type="journal article" year="1914">Distant, 1914</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, are synonymized and moved to the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[917,1044,765,791]" class="Insecta" family="Fulgoridae" genus="Pyrops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="126" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="candelaria">
<emphasis box="[917,1044,765,791]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="126">candelaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group in the present work. As a result, the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Donovan" baseAuthorityYear="1800" box="[333,493,801,827]" class="Insecta" family="Fulgoridae" genus="Pyrops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="126" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pyrorhynchus">
<emphasis box="[333,493,801,827]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="126">pyrorhynchus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group currently contains the following taxa: 
<taxonomicName authority="pythicus" box="[1025,1257,801,827]" class="Insecta" family="Fulgoridae" genus="Pyrops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="126" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="pythicus" subSpecies="pythicus">
<emphasis box="[1025,1257,801,827]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="126">P. pythicus pythicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Schmidt, 1923)" baseAuthorityName="Schmidt" baseAuthorityYear="1923" class="Insecta" family="Fulgoridae" genus="Pyrops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="126" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="pythicus" subSpecies="incertus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="126">P. pythicus incertus</emphasis>
(Schmidt, 1923)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Schmidt, 1926)" baseAuthorityName="Schmidt" baseAuthorityYear="1926" box="[489,781,836,863]" class="Insecta" family="Fulgoridae" genus="Pyrops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="126" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ruehli">
<emphasis box="[489,585,836,862]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="126">P. ruehli</emphasis>
(Schmidt, 1926)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Walker, 1957)" baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1957" box="[791,1111,836,863]" class="Insecta" family="Fulgoridae" genus="Pyrops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="126" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="intricatus">
<emphasis box="[791,929,837,862]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="126">P. intricatus</emphasis>
(Walker, 1957)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Lallemand, 1963)" baseAuthorityName="Lallemand" baseAuthorityYear="1963" class="Insecta" family="Fulgoridae" genus="Pyrops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="126" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="intricatus" subSpecies="albobasalis">
<emphasis box="[1120,1398,836,862]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="126">P. intricatus albobasalis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Lallemand V." box="[197,400,871,898]" pageId="3" pageNumber="126" pagination="1 - 99" refId="ref10944" refString="Lallemand V. 1963. Revision des Fulgoridae (Homoptera). Deuxieme partie. Faunes asiatique et australienne. Memoires de l'Institut royal des Sciences naturelles de Belgique (2 e serie) 75: 1 - 99." type="journal article" year="1963">Lallemand, 1963</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Schmidt, 1907)" baseAuthorityName="Schmidt" baseAuthorityYear="1907" box="[420,755,871,898]" class="Insecta" family="Fulgoridae" genus="Pyrops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="126" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zephyrius">
<emphasis box="[420,559,871,897]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="126">P. zephyrius</emphasis>
(Schmidt, 1907)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Schmidt, 1905)" baseAuthorityName="Schmidt" baseAuthorityYear="1905" box="[810,1115,871,898]" class="Insecta" family="Fulgoridae" genus="Pyrops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="126" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dohrni">
<emphasis box="[810,916,871,897]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="126">P. dohrni</emphasis>
(Schmidt, 1905)
</taxonomicName>
. The status of both latter species will need to be assessed in the future as they do not fully agree with 
<bibRefCitation author="Baker C. F." box="[1094,1271,907,934]" pageId="3" pageNumber="126" pagination="343 - 364" refId="ref9803" refString="Baker C. F. 1925. Remarks on certain Indo-Malayan Fulgora, with special reference to Philippines species. Philippines Journal of Science 28: 343 - 364." type="journal article" year="1925">Baker’s (1925)</bibRefCitation>
definition, for example, the basal third of the posterior wings is not bright blue.
</paragraph>
